CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 20, 1953, page 23, reads: "Business Leader - William Goode, prominent proprietor of the two Goode Pharmacies, gave away several wonderful prizes from this magnetic display which created much interest in McKesson's Drug Products. He was assisted by his charming wife, Mrs. Sarah Goode; Charylene Dudley, Yvonne Nicholas and Eugene Douglas (not shown)."
TitMainTitle: William Goode standing in Goode Pharmacy booth, with Rieck's Dairy booth on right, in Ammon Center for 1953 Pittsburgh Courier Home Service Fair
